page.title: 03Chettiscombe-NE. of Tiverton
page.content: There is a stream which goes into Tiverton and there are lots of farms around this little area. The cars have to go through the stream to go along the lane.There is a bridge, for people, which goes across the stream. It is made of wood. Just beside the stream there are three horsechestnut trees.They have conkers on them and are very big and old.There are old houses and newer ones in Chettiscombe. There is a great big barn by the stream. It looks very old. It is made of stone,like some of the houses in the area.I could not see very many cars about because it is not a main road.It is a country lane which is only used by the local people.I saw some sheep coming along the lane.They went into field.The farmer had two dogs helping him to move the sheep from one field to the other.
